
This example shows how to use pw.x, turbo_lanczos.x, and turbo_spectrum.x
to calculate the absorption spectrum of the CH4 molecule in water
using a fully self-consistent dielectric defined on the electronic density
and using the Liouville-Lanczos approach within the time-dependent density
functional perturbation theory according to 
I. Timrov, O. Andreussi, A. Biancardi, N. Marzari, and S. Baroni, J. Chem. Phys. 142, 034111 (2015).

The description of the keywords for turbo_lanczos.x and tubro_spectrum.x codes 
can be found in TDDFPT/Doc of the Quantum ESPRESSO package.
